FOODBORNE ILLNESS - KYRGYZSTAN: (BISHKEK) SUSHI ROLLS
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 27 Oct 2021
Source: AKI Press [edited]
https://akipress.com/news:664034:Number_of_food_poisoning_victims_in_Bishkek_leaps_to_253/


The total number of people who got food poisoning after they ate sushi rolls in different cafes of Empire of Pizza chain and sought medical assistance has reached 253, the Ministry of Health said. 60 of them remain in hospitals. Their condition is stable. The rest were discharged from hospitals after medical assistance.

After massive food poisoning in Bishkek, all cafes of Empire of Pizza chain were closed for the period of epidemiological investigation. Specialists of the State Sanitary and Epidemiological Center will check all public catering facilities across the country.

